import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load the data from the CSV file
file_path = 'C:\\Users\\req98376\\Downloads\\housing predictaions\\data\\Files used\\zillow_combined_zhvi.csv'
data = pd.read_csv(file_path)
In [9]:
# Get the top 20 counties based on the latest Annual Value of All Homes
latest_year = data['Year_Recorded'].max()
top_20_counties = data[data['Year_Recorded'] == latest_year].nlargest(20, 'AnnualValue_AllHomes')['County']
In [10]:
# Annual Value of All Homes over the Years for Top 20 Counties
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
for county in top_20_counties:
    county_data = data[data['County'] == county]
    plt.plot(county_data['Year_Recorded'].values, county_data['AnnualValue_AllHomes'].values, label=county)
plt.xlabel('Year Recorded')
plt.ylabel('Annual Value of All Homes')
plt.title('Annual Value of All Homes over the Years for Top 20 Counties')

#  legend to the right of the plot
plt.legend(loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.5))
plt.show()
